snippet.textDisplay: Perhaps the biggest lesson in listening to all these heartfelt eulogies is that aside from winning and championships, the relationships across the league and across many sports is profound. The connections, the respect, even the rivalries. At the end of the day, there is love, brotherhood, bonds that span more than 1 generation. That is the takeaway, that is the lesson. Each player has learned from others, had people to look up to, guide them, push them, and just be a witness and participant in their life's journey. THAT is the gift.
